body:
Today we decide to not automatically hide a notification toast if the window has no focus. I believe this is bad for situations where multiple windows are open and VSCode is in the inactive window, but still visible (where today notifications would stack and never hide). 

Ideally we could ask Electron if the window is visible or not and make the decision based on that. This requires https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/20145

